main event: A sighting of three cylinder-shaped brownish objects maneuvering erratically over Fairfield, California on 26 July 1952.
interesting points: The objects were observed climbing to considerable altitudes., The sighting was visual with no radar detection., The witnesses reported the objects maneuvering in an erratic fashion., Weather conditions were clear during the sighting., The report concluded that the objects were not identifiable as known phenomena.
witness description: The witness was Mrs. A. S. C., who observed the objects with the naked eye and binoculars.
